dslRule:
/*!id: collection.init.addall.to.constructor*/
/*!description: Initializes a collection directly in the constructor from another collection, replacing a separate addAll() call.*/
/*!severity: info*/
$Type $var = new $C1<>();
$var.addAll($sourceCollection)
=> new $C1<>($sourceCollection)
;;

/*!id: collection.init.addall.to.constructor.arrays.aslist*/
/*!description: Initializes a collection directly in the constructor from Arrays.asList(), replacing a separate addAll() call.*/
/*!severity: info*/
$Type $var = new $C1<>();
$var.addAll(java.util.Arrays.asList($args$))
=> new $C1<>(java.util.Arrays.asList($args$))
;;

dslRuleAfterChange:
A hypothetical DSL extension could look like:
@id: eclipse.swt.graphics.color.remove-dispose
@severity: info
@tags: eclipse, resource-management, api-migration
@removeStatement:
org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Color.$color.dispose()
;;

This rule would need an additional mechanism to detect and remove the enclosing `if ($color != null)` and `for` loop if `color.dispose()` is the only relevant action, which is not supported.

dslRule:
@id: jdt.internal.formatter.versioner.currentversion.update.to.21
/*!description: Updates the internal formatter profile version from VERSION_20 to VERSION_21.*/
/*!severity: info*/
org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.preferences.formatter.ProfileVersioner.CURRENT_VERSION = org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.preferences.formatter.ProfileVersioner.VERSION_20
=> org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.preferences.formatter.ProfileVersioner.CURRENT_VERSION = org.eclipse.jdt.internal.ui.preferences.formatter.ProfileVersioner.VERSION_21
;;

/*!id: remove.redundant.super.call*/
/*!description: Remove redundant no-argument super() call in constructors (compiler inserts it automatically).*/
/*!severity: info*/
super($args$); :: argsCount($args$, 0)
=>
;;

/*!id: class.make-static-if-no-enclosing-ref*/
/*!description: Makes an inner class static if it does not use a reference to its enclosing instance.*/
/*!severity: info*/
private class $ClassName$ { $Body$ }
:: !isReferencingEnclosingInstance($ClassName$) // Hypothetical guard
=> private static class $ClassName$ { $Body$ }
;;

/*!id: remove.useless.return*/
/*!description: Removes useless 'return;' statements at the end of void methods or lambdas.*/
/*!severity: info*/
return; :: isUselessReturnStatement() // Hypothetical complex guard
=> 
;;

